Keychain
========

A ruby wrapper around some of OS X's keychain functions. The keychain can store several types of information, including internet passwords and generic passwords.

Finding a generic password:

    Keychain.generic_passwords.find :first, :conditions => {:service => 'dummy'}

Finding an internet password:

    Keychain.internet_passwords.find :first, :conditions => {:server => 'dummy.example.com'}

Finding all matching items

    Keychain.internet_passwords.find :all, :conditions => {:server => 'dummy.example.com'}

You can load a keychain with `Keychain.open` or `Keychain.new` or retrive the default keychain with `Keychain.default`


Creating a password:

    #in the default keychain
    Keychain.internet_passwords.add :server => 'dummy.example.com', :password => 'somempasswrd'
    Keychain.generic_passwords.add :service => 'dummy', :password => 'somempasswrd', :account => 'an_account'

    #in a specific keychain

    some_keychain.internet_passwords.add :server => 'dummy.example.com', :password => 'somempasswrd'
    some_keychain.generic_passwords.add :service => 'dummy', :password => 'somempasswrd', :account => 'an_account'

#updating an item

    item = Keychain.internet_passwords.find :first, :conditions => {:server => 'dummy.example.com'}
    item.comment = 'a comment'
    item.password = 'new password'
    item.save